{
  "message": "\ud83d\udc1b docs: cache-bust ACMM badge to force GitHub camo re-fetch\n\nThe first time GitHub's camo proxy fetched the ACMM shields.io URL\n(before the Netlify acmm-badge function was warm), shields.io served\na cached 'inaccessible' badge that camo then pinned for hours.\nAdding &v=2 changes the URL fingerprint enough that camo treats it\nas a new image and re-fetches from shields.io, which now returns the\ncorrect L4 badge.\n\nSigned-off-by: Andrew Anderson <andy@clubanderson.com>",
